  CBD is what gives hemp oil it's pain management qualities.  But like most hemp oil products, you have no idea what you are getting other than possibly the thousands of mg of hemp oil they claim on their label.  Hemp oil extracted from leaves, or stems can have varying amounts of CBD in the oil.  But the oil extracted from the seed has very little.  So when you buy hemp oil keep in mind you have no idea what the CBD content is unless the seller specifically lists it on the label.

My toddler isn't ready for feeding himself a bowl of applesauce yet without a dip in the tub afterward so these work great.
